Want government experience? Have an interest in politics? Apply to our internship program for the spring in both DC and San Diego! Check out how to apply and who to contact here:
 https://susandavis.house.gov/constituent-services/internships.htm … pic.twitter.com/mjLAJsazbI

The @EdLaborCmte today passed the #CollegeAffordabilityAct with my amendment to provide the single greatest increase for Pell grants in history. This legislation will increase access, affordability, and accountability while preparing students for the jobs of tomorrow.

The President endangered our national security for his personal political gain. I just voted to move the impeachment inquiry to the next phase. The American people will begin to hear firsthand about the abuse of power committed by President Trump. #DefendOurDemocracy

The House will vote today on legislation to protect our environment, including a bill to ban mining on nearly one million acres of public land around the Grand Canyon. We must protect these national treasures! #PeopleOverPolluters pic.twitter.com/hIGKTWx3jz

Breast cancer mortality rates have dropped 40% since 1989 thanks to raising awareness and funding for research into finding a cure. Join me and my colleagues, wearing pink for #BreastCancerAwarenessMonth, in working to see that these rates continue to decrease. pic.twitter.com/5RvHN1fGyv

Aging Americans including many low-income seniors are not receiving the support they need. Today, the House is voting on the Dignity in Aging Act, which would increase funding for all Older Americans Act programs. pic.twitter.com/wVa3orA1q7

Thank you to those who participated in my latest survey.  We had over 7,500 responses!  Although this is not a scientific survey, I’m glad many of you made your voices heard.  Here are the results. pic.twitter.com/tEdFOOAyhB

One year ago today 11 people were massacred for being Jewish while praying at the #TreeofLife
Synagogue. Today we remember those we lost. Anti-Semitism is real and active in our country, but we are stronger than hate.

Gratitude to our well-trained & accomplished military & national security professionals, as well as our allies, for bringing Baghdadi down. The world is grateful for this barbarian’s end. Hopefully, this brings some relief to the families of his victims. https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/national-security/us-forces-launch-operation-in-syria-targeting-isis-leader-baghdadi-officials-say/2019/10/27/081bc257-adf1-4db6-9a6a-9b820dd9e32d_story.html …

The Department's job is to prioritize students over for-profits schools. Now a federal judge has sanctioned the Department for its failure to protect borrowers. It's time for the Secretary to finally put students first. https://www.nytimes.com/2019/10/24/us/politics/education-dept-loan-repayments-corinthian.html …
I was honored to attend services for Congressman Elijah Cummings where President Obama praised his work and legacy. pic.twitter.com/zkupbMnDRr

The House is working hard to make sure the election interference we saw in 2016 doesn't happen again. First, we passed the #SAFEAct to protect our election infrastructure. Today, we will pass the #SHIELDAct to keep foreign governments from trying to influence our elections. pic.twitter.com/R19gPgYkP7

I'll be voting for the #PACTAct today to make animal abuse a federal crime. While making and/or distributing animal crush videos is a federal crime, there is no law against the underlying act of cruelty against animals. Animal abuse has no place in our society. #ProtectOurPets pic.twitter.com/lf29f3mXQG
Happy first birthday in Congress to my friend and colleague @RepMikeLevin! pic.twitter.com/6XAll0XYLu

Thank you @USIP for hosting a bipartisan discussion on what’s next for democracy & women’s rights in Afghanistan. Proud to join my friend @RepMarthaRoby to talk about the future of Afghanistan & the women working for a lasting peace for their country. #BipartisanUSIP pic.twitter.com/zhWwRySCrx

The @EdLaborCmte advanced, with my strong support, the #LowerDrugCosts Now Act (H.R. 3). This legislation will allow the government to negotiate lower drug prices on behalf of the American people, saving over $440 billion for Medicare, private employers, and American workers.

What an irreplaceable loss to our country! Elijah was such a stellar human being in every way. His very presence and demeanor spoke words of moral authority and love for the people he served. My heartfelt condolences to his wonderful family who shared his strength with all of us. pic.twitter.com/QCSnFyyoUk

Just voted to condemn President Trump's disastrous decision that has added to an already dangerous situation in the Middle East. https://www.washingtonpost.com/politics/trump-tries-to-distance-us-from-chaos-in-syria-says-kurdish-allies-are-no-angels/2019/10/16/7b6c5ac8-f037-11e9-b2da-606ba1ef30e3_story.html …
Thank you to @SDFD and @SanDiegoPD for their swift response to the Kensington/Talmadge fire. https://fox5sandiego.com/2019/10/15/crews-work-to-put-out-brush-fire/ …

Today, @EdLaborCmte introduced a bold proposal to lower higher education costs and give students stronger support to graduate. The #CollegeAffordabilityAct is a comprehensive plan so students spend less and earn more. pic.twitter.com/c9ZQh6hcsp

The House has passed dozens of major bills - such as to lower health care & prescription drug prices, end corruption, raise wages, and address gun violence - only to have Senate Majority Leader McConnell block them in the Senate. Time for Senate obstruction to end. #ForThePeople pic.twitter.com/KD12VTWeIm

Proud to lead the effort in Congress to include a basic needs allowance to end military hunger among our servicemembers. The Supreme Court just took up an abortion rights case challenging a clinic shutdown law in Louisiana. #SCOTUS ruled that an identical law in Texas was unconstitutional just three years ago. Abortion is #MyRightMyDecision, #SCOTUS must protect it.

Talked with 11th and 12th graders at Monte Vista High School in Spring Valley. We discussed the importance of getting involved in the community. It was great to be able to speak with students about the issues that matter to them and answer their questions about Congress. pic.twitter.com/Q6pYYUR8mO
